metadata.title: Cessna 206
aws::graph::propositions: Cessna 206 and 207 Aircraft Model Features and Production
Cessna 206 introduced removeable rear cabin air outlets in 1975.
Cessna 206 introduced a revised glareshield in 1975.
207A Skywagon 207/Stationair 7/Stationair 8 was introduced for the 1977 model year.
207A Skywagon 207/Stationair 7/Stationair 8 featured an improved Vernier mixture control.
207A Skywagon 207/Stationair 7/Stationair 8 featured a rectangular hour meter.
207A Skywagon 207/Stationair 7/Stationair 8 featured an improved aileron control system.
T207's engine was changed to a 310 hp (231 kW) Continental TSIO-520-M.

text:
1975 introduced removeable rear cabin air outlets and a revised glareshield.  Certified on December 31, 1968.  362 total built; 148 (1969), 42 (1970), 15 (1971), 10 (1972), 12 (1973), 40 (1974), 47 (1975), and 48 (1976).
207A Skywagon 207/Stationair 7/Stationair 8
Introduced for the 1977 model year with an improved Vernier mixture control, energy-absorbing instrument subpanels, a rectangular hour meter, and an improved aileron control system.  The T207's engine was also changed to a 310 hp (231 kW) Continental TSIO-520-M.
